org.kepler.gui

Interface TabPane

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    TabPaneActionListener
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ActorFireOutlineTabPane, BasicLibraryPane, CacheViewerTabPane, ComponentLibraryTab, CurrentExecutionPanel, DatasetPanel, ExecutionMonitorPanel, ItemsOfInterestPanel, PlotsEditorPanel, PlotsPanel, PortIOOutlineTabPane, PreviousExecutionPanel, PropertiesPanel, ReportDesignerPanel, ReportViewerPanel, ReportViewerTOC, TabPaneExtensionExample, ViewWatchingTabPane, WorkflowOutlineTabPane, WorkflowRunManagerPanel, WorkflowRunOutlineTabPane, WorkflowSchedulerComponentLibraryTab, WorkflowSchedulerParentPanel, WorkflowSchedulerServerInstallationInfoPanel

    public interface TabPane
    This interface is to be implemented by anyone wanting to add a tab to the Kepler. The TabPaneFactory generates instances of TabPane.
    Author:
    Aaron Schultz

    • Method Detail

      • initializeTab

        void initializeTab()
            throws java.lang.Exception
        Initialization of the tab should be done at some point after the constructor is called. The setParentFrame() method is called by the factory before calling initializeTab(). This also allows for more easily adding new functions to this interface later on.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
